<h1 class="fw-bold h1 text-center" style="margin-top: 2rem; color:#16b7c7">Welcome to my website!</h1>

- - -

I am a PhD candidate at [LIP6](https://www.lip6.fr/), Sorbonne Université, where I work in teams **SMA** (Multiagent systems) and **Decision** under the supervision of [Nawal BENABBOU](https://benabbou.lip6.fr/), [Aurélie BEYNIER](https://webia.lip6.fr/~beyniera/), [Nicolas MAUDET](https://nmaudet.gitlab.io/).

My research lies in a field called [Computational Social Choice](https://comsoc-community.org/) which aims at developing the mathematical and algorithmic tools to do collective decision making. It deals with numerous (super interesting!) problems, for instance: voting theory, fair allocation, matching, judgement aggregation, and much more. In particular, my PhD focuses on fair division, a topic where we wonder about how to fairly allocate a set of resources to some agents, or groups of agents. It requires to mathematically formalize the idea of fairness, and to design algorithms to achieve such fairness. 

In my PhD thesis, I am focusing on proposing a new kind of models in fair allocation: **Multilevel Fair Allocation**. This model allows to deal with fair allocation problem in hierarchical structure, a problem mostly not addressed in the current literature. 

I have also a broader interest for decision theory, operations research, and network theory (among many other interests). Feel free to reach out if these topics interest you. 

